    ) VALUES (1471569, 'Stiripentol', 'Ondansetron', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with stiripentol may increase the plasma concentrations of ondansetron. The interaction has not been studied nor reported, and clinical significance is unknown. According to the prescribing information, ondansetron is metabolized by CYP450 3A4, 2D6 and 1A2. Due to the multiple routes of metabolism, inhibition or reduced activity (e.g., CYP450 2D6 genetic deficiency) of one metabolic pathway is normally compensated by other pathways and is not expected to cause significant change in overall ondansetron clearance or dose requirement. However, stiripentol is an inhibitor of CYP450 3A4 and has also been shown to inhibit CYP450 2D6 and 1A2 in vitro, thus a pharmacokinetic interaction is theoretically possible if all three routes of ondansetron metabolism are significantly inhibited.', NULL, 'Caution may be advisable if ondansetron is coadministered with stiripentol.', NULL, 'Caution may be advisable if ondansetron is coadministered with stiripentol. Patients should be monitored more closely for serious adverse effects of ondansetron such as QT prolongation and serotonin syndrome.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317476);
